<section xml:id="Ethics_Core_Concepts">
  <title>Core Concepts</title>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>
        As Stephen Gardiner notes,
        <q>we cannot get very far in discussing why climate change is a problem without invoking ethical considerations.</q>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Climate change is a long-term global-scale problem caused by short-term,
        local-scale actions.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Some problems, like climate change,
        have no technical solutions, but only behavioral ones
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Some problems, like climate change,
        require collective actions to solve.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>